21 schools as stated in KRS 158.6451, including reducing the achievement gaps as
22 determined by an equity analysis of the disaggregated student performance data
23 from the state assessment program developed under KRS 158.6453; engage
24 educators in effective learning processes and foster collegiality and collaboration;
25 and provide support for staff to incorporate newly acquired skills into their work
