21 to appear and answer the charges, the Kentucky Board of Education may remove
22 the officer by a majority vote, and the dismissal shall be final.
23 (6) The hearing shall be public or private at the discretion of the accused former or
24 current superintendent and shall be public when testimony is taken for board
25 members.
26 (7) The Kentucky Board of Education may meet in closed session to consider the
27 evidence and may by a majority vote remove the officer. If the board votes to
